[h1] Custom fonts

[p-]
Load custom fonts from podnet and use them on headings, paragraphs,
and links. Declare all fonts at the top of your file (right after the
meta block) before any tag uses them.
[-p]

[code-]
[font id=fancy url=podnet://78402/fonts/widesquat.font height=10]
[font id=wide  url=podnet://78402/fonts/lilwide.font   height=8]
[-code]

[p] Reference a font by its id using the font= property on any supported tag:

[code-]
[h1 font=fancy] Title in fancy font
[h2 font=wide]  Section in wide font
[h3 font=fancy] Sub-section in fancy font
[p  font=fancy] A short paragraph in the fancy font.
[p- font=fancy]
A multi-line paragraph
in the fancy font.
[-p]
[link file=other.podweb font=wide] Link label in wide font
[-code]

[h2] height

[p-]
The height= value is the pixel height of the font characters.
Line spacing is height + 2 pixels.
If the font URL cannot be fetched, the browser silently falls back
to the default font - so a broken URL will never crash your page.
[-p]

[p] Looking for fonts to use? Check out this collection:

[link user=78402 file=podweb/fonts.podweb] great fonts by thelxinoe5

